  "prompt": "What should every first time anime convention goer know?",
  "response": "Attending your first anime convention can be an exciting experience! Here are some essential tips for first-time attendees:\n\n### Before the Convention\n\n1. **Research the Event**: Understand the convention's schedule, layout, and guests. Check the schedule for panels, events, and workshops that interest you.\n\n2. **Purchase Tickets Early**: Buy your tickets in advance, as prices may be higher at the door or may sell out.\n\n3. **Plan Your Cosplay or Outfit**: If you plan to cosplay, choose something comfortable and appropriate for the event. Also, consider the weather and venue conditions.\n\n4. **Pack Essentials**: Bring essentials like water, snacks, a power bank for your phone, a notepad for autographs, and any cosplay props.\n\n5. **Budget**: Set aside money for merchandise, food, and any activities you might want to participate in, such as photo ops or workshops.\n\n### During the Convention\n\n6. **Arrive Early**: Get there early to avoid long lines and to get familiar with the layout.\n\n7. **Stay Hydrated and Nourished**: Drink plenty of water and take breaks to eat. Convention food can be pricey, so consider packing some snacks.\n\n8. **Respect the Venue and Others**: Be mindful of your surroundings, keep noise levels down in panels, and respect other attendees' personal space as well as their cosplay.\n\n9. **Engage with Other Fans**: Don\u2019t hesitate to strike up conversations and make new friends. Most attendees are friendly and excited to share their interests.\n\n10. **Explore and Enjoy**: Take time to explore vendor booths, artist alleys, and other events. You never know what surprise finds or experiences await you.\n\n### While Cosplaying\n\n11. **Comfort Matters**: Ensure that your cosplay is comfortable and suitable for moving around. Be prepared for reactions, both positive and negative.\n\n12. **Photo Etiquette**: If you want to take photos with others or of others, always ask for permission first. Be respectful of cosplayers' boundaries.\n\n### General Tips\n\n13. **Follow Convention Rules**: Each convention has its own rules regarding photography, cosplay, and behavior. Familiarize yourself with them and follow the guidelines.\n\n14. **Plan for Downtime**: Conventions can be overwhelming, so it\u2019s okay to take a break and relax in designated areas.\n\n15. **Have Fun**: Remember that conventions are about enjoying your interests and meeting others who share your passions. Embrace the experience!\n\n### After the Convention\n\n16. **Stay Connected**: Exchange social media handles with new friends and keep in touch. Many conventions also have online communities where you can connect with attendees post-event.\n\n17. **Reflect and Share**: After the convention, share your experiences and photos with others. It helps build community and prepares you for the next event!\n\nBy following these tips, you can have a fun and memorable first experience at an anime convention! Enjoy!",
